# Copy to ".env" in this directory (repo root, next to docker-compose.yml).
# Docker Compose loads this file into the `ai` container via `env_file` (optional).
# Interpolation `${GEMINI_API_KEY}` in compose also reads this `.env` — avoid wrapping
# secrets in quotes unless you intend quotes to be part of the value.

# --- Gemini (primary narrative / LaTeX generation) ---
# https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs
GEMINI_API_KEY=
# Narrative path: URL context on SearXNG headline URLs only (no Google Search). Examples: gemini-2.5-flash
# Peer-review dialogue rounds (Critic ↔ Junior LaTeX revision) before Lead PM; 1–4, default 2.
# PEER_REVIEW_ROUNDS=2
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash
# On 429, WARNING logs append QuotaFailure[metric=...; id=...] when Google includes it in the
# error JSON; many responses only carry Help links — then logs explain that RPM/TPM/RPD is unknown from the payload.
# Slow down Gemini when you see 429 RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED (all seconds, floats OK).
# GEMINI_RETRY_BACKOFF_BASE_SEC=5
# GEMINI_RETRY_BACKOFF_MULT=2
# GEMINI_RETRY_BACKOFF_MAX_SEC=120
# Pause before the first narrative stream call:
# GEMINI_PREFLIGHT_DELAY_SEC=2
# Pause between tool presets (Search+URL → Search-only):
# GEMINI_BETWEEN_TOOL_PRESETS_SEC=5
# Pause between Junior → Critic → Lead PM (same API key):
# GEMINI_BETWEEN_AGENTS_SEC=8
# Lead PM only: extra retries on 503/429 (default 8, clamped 3–15; uses GEMINI_RETRY_BACKOFF_* sleeps).
# LEAD_PM_GEMINI_MAX_ATTEMPTS=8
# Outer PDF LaTeX repair loop when repair still returns transient errors:
# GEMINI_PDF_REPAIR_STAGGER_BASE_SEC=12
# GEMINI_PDF_REPAIR_STAGGER_MAX_SEC=60
# AI service logs (gunicorn + app): DEBUG shows Gemini stack traces on failures.
# LOG_LEVEL=INFO
# Interval (seconds) for SSE ``: keepalive`` comments during /report/stream (avoids Gunicorn WORKER TIMEOUT).
# SSE_HEARTBEAT_SEC=20

# Market history uses yfinance (no separate API key).

# --- SearXNG (headlines) ---
# In Docker Compose the default is http://searxng:8080 (service DNS on the compose network).
# If you run the Flask AI app on the host, use http://127.0.0.1:8080 (host-published port).
# From *inside* the `ai` container, do not use 127.0.0.1 to reach SearXNG — use `searxng:8080`.
# Optional extra bases (comma-separated), e.g. SEARXNG_FALLBACK_URLS=http://192.168.1.5:8080
# SEARXNG_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080
# Sent on every JSON search as X-Forwarded-For / X-Real-IP (quiets botdetection header warnings).
# SEARXNG_CLIENT_IP=127.0.0.1
# Pause between planned headline queries to reduce upstream engine 429s (seconds).
# SEARXNG_QUERY_DELAY_SEC=0.35

# --- SEC EDGAR (required descriptive User-Agent) ---
# https://www.sec.gov/os/accessing-edgar-data
SEC_USER_AGENT=YourCompany ProjectSentinel/1.0 (mailto:you@example.com)

# Suggested additional sources (not wired yet; good next integrations):
# - FRED (macro): https://fred.stlouisfed.org/docs/api/api_key.html
# - Polygon.io (alt market + fundamentals): https://polygon.io/
# - OpenFIGI / FactSet symbology for class-action / ADR mapping
# - SEC full-text search API for MD&A snippets (heavier compliance surface)
